CISC 3300 F24 
In class assignment 3 
1. The HTML _id_ attribute is used to specify a unique _id_ for an HTML element 
2. The HTML _div_ tag is a block-level element used for grouping and structuring content. 
3. CSS __declarations__ have a property and a value and apply a visual effect. 
4. CSS _selectors_ are used to "find" (or select) the HTML elements you want to style 
5. If there are two or more CSS rules that point to the same element, the selector with the highest _specificity_ will "win". 
6. HTML treats every element as living in its own _box_. 
7. The __padding__ property allows you to specify how much space should appear between the content of an element and its border 
8. _Text-align_ is useful for centering inline block elements 
9. Setting a CSS rule of display: _block_ will cause it to start on a new line, and takes up the whole width 
10. Create an HTML page with a div element that contains three children div elements. The children div elements should: 
● sit side by side on one line 
● be centered in the middle of the page 
● be 100px wide and 100px tall 
● have a margin of 5px on all sides 
● have a solid black border 1px in width.
